# 🎬 Movie Clipper — TikTok Scene Generator

CLI tool to:
✅ Read list of movies  
✅ Ask ChatGPT for popular scenes  
✅ Auto-detect actual scenes with PySceneDetect  
✅ Clip and burn subtitles (default ON)  
✅ Output vertical 1080x1920 clips for TikTok  

---

## ⚙️ Setup (Mac)

### 1️⃣ Install dependencies

```bash
# Install ffmpeg
brew install ffmpeg

# Install Python and PySceneDetect
brew install python

# Create virtual environment
python3 -m venv venv

# Activate the virtual environment
source venv/bin/activate

# Install PySceneDetect
pip install scenedetect

# Install Node.js deps
npm install


CLI options
Option	Description
--mock	Use mock static response (no API calls)
--no-subs	Disable subtitles in output clips
--max-scenes=N	Limit number of scenes to generate (default: 4)

🧪 Mock mode (for testing without API calls)

You can run movie-clipper in mock mode to test the entire pipeline without making requests to OpenAI.

This is useful for:
✅ Testing clipping logic
✅ Testing scene detection
✅ Avoiding API costs during development
🚀 How to run in mock mode

source venv/bin/activate
node index.js movies.json --mock

What happens:

    The program will return a static example response for getPopularScenes().

    No API calls will be made.

    The rest of the program runs as normal — scene detection, clipping, etc.